23:
I will not give you any orders.
I will not do what you want me to do.
34:
Part of a captain's job is knowing
which troops NOT to send to the
front lines—Stella would be one of
those.
46:
Yep. Sounds like the adventurers did
well too—I can hear them hooting
and hollering from all the way over
here.
50: I wonder what our losses were like...
55:
Definitely not zero. Don't get your
hopes up.
58:
It's good to reflect on your own
actions. But don't let that be an
excuse to stand around and do
nothing, you hear?
60:
Ah, sorry about that. When I see a
young face like yours on the
battlefield, I just instinctively start
lecturing. Comes with age.
65:
Thank you, Zekhel. You've been a
huge help to us this whole time.
68:
Come on, you can't go and say
something like that right to my face.
I'm turning red here.
72:
With the lance gone, and the
original Stella broken, I was worried
that our luck might have run dry.
75:
But it seems we managed to pull
through. Perhaps this was for the
best.
81:
Were you able to find a place for the
Vesta to live?
84:
A group called the Gargans have
invited us to stay with them. I am
grateful for their hospitality.
89:
They debated going back to our
home world, but decided against it.
The merge with Pandemonium is
only getting worse, after all.
93:
Returning now might only sow the
seeds of further conflict. I, for one,
agree with the Vesta's decision.
98:
They'll do just fine over here. They've
certainly made a name for
themselves—now all Palpebra
knows just how strong they are.
100:
The people will treat them better. It
would have been nice if that were
the case from the start, but hey.
104:
Heh. Not to be smug, but I'm pretty
sure that's exactly what I suggested
they do earlier.
107:
That, and people have finally come
to realize that the Vesta aren't an
unreasonable people.
111:
I wonder if you had a hand in
making that happen...
114:
Me? Nah. Those ladies did it all. They
proved themselves on their own.
119:
The miniscule woman from the
Guild!
Is it okay for her to be here?
123: Yes. I asked her to come.
127: We need her to learn the truth.
130:
Welcome to Starview Village, Dul
Kugala.
139:
A village overlooking multiple
worlds. I see... I had read of such a
place in the stories the guide left
behind.
142:
Such legends were once considered
mere superstition... That all
changed, of course, after the
discovery of the Kaleidoscope.
144:
We had already started looking into
the matter, you know. We assumed
that people such as yourselves
existed, somewhere out there.
147:
So, basically you've been watching
us from the start?
151:
Yes. But we came to the conclusion
that you were a force for good.
Hence why we tried to improve
relations with you.
155: ...Is that what you were trying to do?
159:
Pretty sure you were straight up
hostile to us at one point there.
164:
There was no hostility or deception
in our actions. We merely presented
you with our terms.
169:
You really ought to work on your
people skills, Kugala. Just saying.
174: I... cannot help it if I speak candidly!
177:
But don't make the mistake of
assuming the other Guild members
are just like me.
180:
They're unscrupulous and enigmatic
to the core. I would tread carefully
and avoid divulging too much
information.
184:
We understand. That's why we
wanted you to be the one to come
here.
188: I... suppose I am glad to be here.
192:
Her Oudo resonates with great
embarrassment!
197:
With regards to the Sheephird
legends, I've told everything I know
to Mal Lelucia.
199:
If there's something you wish to
know, you may ask her.
203:
I take this invitation as a sign I have
earned your trust. I hope that we
may foster an even stronger bond in
the future.
207:
Well, I guess I might as well get
going too.
212:
I'm just a grumpy old man, so you
can feel free to ignore what I'm
about to say, but...
215:
Don't go thinking that things are
always going to work out like this.
219:
Day's gonna come when you have
to make some tough choices.
222:
Then the things you don't
choose—the things you leave
behind—they'll worm their way down
into your heart and stay there.
224:
But don't let that stop you from
moving forward. Keep doing your
best, if that's what you want to do.
232:
Ah, the vigor and pep that comes
with youth. Takes me back.
236:
Hero of the Red Soup.
You don't need to worry. You are a
good man.
244:
I know it to be true. I have heard
your Oudo, and it is both strong and
gentle.
246:
I will endeavor to be like you, hero. I
wish to search for my path forward,
instead of relying solely on my blade.
250:
You've taught me this. For that, and
much more, you should be proud of
yourself.
265: Of course. Let's do just that.
